                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>On October 12 President Truman signed Executive Order 10177, transferring the
                    United States occupation functions in Austria from the Department of the Army to
                    the Department of State with the exception of military matters which would
                    remain the province of the Commanding General, effective October 16. Walter J.
                    Donnelly, who had been nominated for the post in August, took up the position as
                    United States High Commissioner for Austria from that date, replacing General
                    Keyes. A copy of the Executive Order is in file 768.0221/10–1350, or see
                    Department of State <hi rend="italic">Bulletin</hi>, October 23, 1950, page
                    679.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
